  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Emergency Response in Slovakia to People Fleeing the Conflict in Ukraine</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Following the beginning of the recent conflict in Ukraine on 24 February 2022, substantive flows and displacements across Ukraine and toward neighbouring countries have been reported. Hundreds of thousands of people have been forced to flee their homes in search of safety. The needs of vulnerable and displaced persons are increasing drastically. The Slovak Republic shares a 97,852km land border with Ukraine. Since 24 February there has been a tenfold increase in arrivals. Besides Third Country Nationals who represent around 12% of persons, there are mainly Ukrainian women with children, elderly and unaccompanied minors crossing the Slovak border as Ukraine has announced mobilization of men between 18 and 60 years old. Through this project, IOM is providing immediate support to conflict-affected individuals at the Slovak-Ukrainian border including provision of direct assistance of relief resources, transport, referrals to durable safe and accessible accommodation facilities, provision of essential needs to beneficiaries, as well as relevant data gathering.</narrative>
  </description>
